sense.definition:
 (denom. of לֵב) 
to encourage; 
to strengthen.

sense.notes:
) 
to knock about, to send from place to place. Mekh. B’shall., Amal., s. 2 שאברהם לא לְבָטוּהוּ when Abraham was to be shown the holy land (Gen. XIII, 14) they did not trouble him to leave his place, ומשה לְבָטוּהוּ but Moses they did put to the trouble &c. (Deut. III, 27).—Part. pass. לָבוּט, pl. לְבוּטִים 
outcasts. Gen. R. s. 52, beg., v. next w.

sense.definition:
 לוּלָבִין twigs used as 
brooms in the wine press (Rashi), cmp. אַלְבִּינָא; 
the two posts supporting the beams of the press (Ar.).

teaching, learning, study (interch. with תלמוד); 
training; 
habit.

to gather, glean; 
to pick, v. 
Pi.—Part.

 c. (לְקשׁ) 
slow, late (in the season); 
late rain; late-born (cmp. אָפִיל).
